diff --git a/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..2d1c5162
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ROOT-SECURITY-RELEASE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,195 @@
+# False Positive Report: CVE-2026-42217 (OpenEXR) on Debian 11 "bullseye"
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| **CVE** | CVE-2026-42217 |
+| **GHSA** | GHSA-3c67-4wwp-w52m |
+| **Component flagged** | `openexr` 2.5.4 (Debian 11 "bullseye") |
+| **Scanner verdict** | Vulnerable |
+| **Investigated verdict** | **NOT AFFECTED — False positive** |
+| **VEX justification** | `vulnerable_code_not_present` |
+| **Date assessed** | 2026-06-08 |
+
+---
+
+## 1. Summary
+
+CVE-2026-42217 is reported by the scanner against the `openexr` 2.5.4 package
+shipped in Debian 11 "bullseye". After source-level verification, this is a
+**false positive**. The vulnerable code does not exist in OpenEXR 2.5.x. The
+affected feature (IDManifest) was introduced in OpenEXR **3.0.0**, which is a
+later major version than the one bullseye ships. There is no reachable code
+path, so there is nothing to exploit and nothing to patch.
+
+The correct status for the bullseye `openexr` source package is
+**`not-affected`** (Debian terminology) / **`not_affected`** (VEX), not
+"vulnerable, fix pending."
+
+---
+
+## 2. The vulnerability
+
+CVE-2026-42217 is a shift-exponent overflow (undefined behavior) in the
+function `readVariableLengthInteger()` in `ImfIDManifest.cpp`. When parsing an
+untrusted EXR file, a variable-length integer with excessive continuation bytes
+can drive the shift amount to `>= 64`, making `(byte & 127) << shift` undefined
+behavior on a 64-bit value, which can yield corrupted length values during
+IDManifest string-list parsing.
+
+- **Severity:** MEDIUM, CVSS v4.0 base score 6.3
+- **Affected versions (per advisory):** 3.0.0–3.2.8, 3.3.0–3.3.10, 3.4.0–3.4.10
+- **Fixed versions:** 3.2.9, 3.3.11, 3.4.11
+- **Upstream fix commit:** `21eaa33bcbbb0c83a5fc42f6b6d65b70a996e63c` (PR #2378)
+
+The fix adds a guard before the shift:
+
+```cpp
+// Each chunk contributes at most 7 bits; shifts must stay < 64 or
+// (byte & 127) << shift has undefined behavior (C++).
+if (shift >= 64)
+{
+    throw IEX_NAMESPACE::InputExc (
+        "Invalid variable-length integer in IDManifest");
+}
+```
+
+**Note the lower bound of the affected range: 3.0.0.** Bullseye's 2.5.4 sits
+below this floor.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Why bullseye (2.5.4) is not affected
+
+The entire IDManifest feature — the file `ImfIDManifest.cpp` and the vulnerable
+`readVariableLengthInteger()` function — was **added in OpenEXR 3.0.0** and does
+not exist in any 2.5.x release.
+
+### 3.1 The feature was introduced after 2.5.x
+
+The IDManifest support was added in a single upstream commit:
+
+```
+commit c61ddf27  —  "Add idmanifest attribute support (#909)"
+date:   2021-02-14
+```
+
+The earliest release tag that contains that commit is **v3.0.0-beta / v3.0.1**:
+
+```
+$ git tag --contains c61ddf27 | sort -V | head
+v3.0.0-beta
+v3.0.1
+v3.0.1-beta
+v3.0.2
+...
+```
+
+No `v2.5.*` tag contains it.
+
+### 3.2 The vulnerable file/function is absent from 2.5.4
+
+```
+$ git grep -l "readVariableLengthInteger" v2.5.4
+NOT PRESENT in v2.5.4
+
+$ git ls-tree -r --name-only v2.5.4 | grep -i manifest
+(no output)
+```
+
+For contrast, the same symbol is present in 3.x:
+
+```
+$ git grep -l "readVariableLengthInteger" v3.1.0
+v3.1.0:src/lib/OpenEXR/ImfIDManifest.cpp
+```
+
+### 3.3 Conclusion of the source review
+
+Because `ImfIDManifest.cpp` and `readVariableLengthInteger()` do not exist in
+2.5.4:
+
+- There is no code path that performs the offending `<< shift` operation.
+- The undefined-behavior shift cannot be triggered by any input.
+- A backport of fix commit `21eaa33b` **cannot apply** — there is no matching
+  file or function to patch.
+
+This is "vulnerable code not present," the strongest form of not-affected.
+
+---
+
+## 4. Why the scanner flagged it anyway
+
+This is a classic version-range matching artifact for distribution packages:
+
+- Most scanners match a finding by **package name + version** against the
+  affected ranges in CVE/NVD metadata.
+- If that metadata is recorded without a correct lower bound (e.g. as
+  `openexr < 3.4.11` or with no minimum version), any older version — including
+  2.5.4 — matches the rule and is flagged.
+- The **real** affected range starts at **3.0.0**, the release where the
+  vulnerable feature first appeared. 2.5.4 predates it.
+
+The scanner is matching metadata, not the actual presence of vulnerable code.
+Hence the false positive.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Verification steps (reproducible)
+
+Run inside an OpenEXR git checkout that has the release tags:
+
+```bash
+# 1. Confirm the vulnerable symbol does not exist in 2.5.4
+git grep -l "readVariableLengthInteger" v2.5.4        # -> no match
+
+# 2. Confirm the IDManifest file does not exist in 2.5.4
+git ls-tree -r --name-only v2.5.4 | grep -i manifest  # -> no output
+
+# 3. Confirm when the feature was introduced
+git log --oneline --diff-filter=A --all -- '*ImfIDManifest.cpp'
+# -> c61ddf27 Add idmanifest attribute support (#909)
+
+# 4. Confirm the first release that contains it (>= 3.0.0)
+git tag --contains c61ddf27 | sort -V | head
+# -> v3.0.0-beta, v3.0.1, ...
+
+# 5. (Optional) Confirm the symbol IS present in 3.x for contrast
+git grep -l "readVariableLengthInteger" v3.1.0
+# -> v3.1.0:src/lib/OpenEXR/ImfIDManifest.cpp
+```
+
+---
+
+## 6. Recommended classification
+
+| Framework | Status to record | Justification / note |
+|-----------|------------------|----------------------|
+| Debian security tracker | `<not-affected>` | "Vulnerable IDManifest code introduced in 3.0.0; not present in 2.5.x (bullseye)." |
+| CycloneDX / CSAF VEX | `not_affected` | `vulnerable_code_not_present` |
+| Generic scanner suppression | Suppress / mark FP | Version 2.5.4 predates the affected 3.0.0+ range. |
+
+---
+
+## 7. Caveat before closing
+
+Confirm the scanned artifact is genuinely built from the bullseye `openexr`
+2.5.4 **source package**, and not a **bundled/vendored copy** of a 3.x OpenEXR
+embedded inside another product. If a 3.x copy (3.0.0–3.4.10) is present
+anywhere on the system, that copy *is* affected and must be updated to
+3.2.9 / 3.3.11 / 3.4.11 or patched with upstream commit `21eaa33b`.
+
+If the package is confirmed to be 2.5.4, this CVE is a false positive and can be
+closed as not-affected.
+
+---
+
+## 8. References
+
+- CVE record: https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-42217
+- Advisory (GHSA-3c67-4wwp-w52m):
+  https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/security/advisories/GHSA-3c67-4wwp-w52m
+- Fix PR #2378:
+  https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/pull/2378
+- Fix commit:
+  https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/21eaa33bcbbb0c83a5fc42f6b6d65b70a996e63c
+- Feature-introducing commit (c61ddf27, "Add idmanifest attribute support", #909)
Description: CVE-2026-40244 - Fix integer overflow in DWA compressor
 Cast width and height to size_t before multiplication to prevent
 integer overflow in pointer offset computation. The width and height
 fields are int (32-bit), and their product can overflow when computing
 buffer offsets, leading to heap corruption.
 .
 This is the backport of the upstream fix to the OpenEXR 2.x codebase,
 where the equivalent code lives in ImfDwaCompressor.cpp (C++ class)
 rather than internal_dwa_compressor.h (C API) in OpenEXR 3.x.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openexr/commit/419f483fb16661a70db84e90c8ca236e7d20a4fc
Author: Cary Phillips <cary@ilm.com>
Last-Update: 2026-04-23

--- a/OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfDwaCompressor.cpp
+++ b/OpenEXR/IlmImf/ImfDwaCompressor.cpp
@@ -2666,7 +2666,8 @@
                 continue;

             rowPtrs[chan].push_back (outBufferEnd);
-            outBufferEnd += cd->width * OPENEXR_IMF_NAMESPACE::pixelTypeSize (cd->type);
+            outBufferEnd +=
+                (size_t) cd->width * (size_t) OPENEXR_IMF_NAMESPACE::pixelTypeSize (cd->type);
         }
